1
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,605
What's the matter, Sakura?

2
00:01:45,688 --> 00:01:47,690
-Get off of me already!
-Stomachache?

3
00:01:47,774 --> 00:01:50,735
You've sure got some guts
to use me as your horse!

4
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,946
Morning, Kotoha-chan!

5
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:54,823
Granny Sato!

6
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:56,116
I said get off!

7
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:58,910
Are you telling me to jump off
from this height?

8
00:01:58,993 --> 00:02:01,246
Be more considerate of your elders, boy.

9
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:02,872
I'll slam you down, granny!

10
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,542
Goodness, you're so inconsiderate.

11
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:11,297
Huh? You said you had lower back pain
so you couldn't stand!

12
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,508
Ow, it hurts so much.

13
00:02:13,591 --> 00:02:16,636
My lower back is in so much pain
I could only get this far.

14
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:19,055
You liar! You're as healthy as one can be!

15
00:02:20,181 --> 00:02:21,516
But still...

16
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:25,019
Even with all the complaints,
you're still a Furin kid.

17
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:28,189
You were a great help. Thank you.

18
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:32,694
Damn it! I'm leaving!

19
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:34,487
Hey, Sakura. Hold up.

20
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:35,655
What is it?

21
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:39,784
Fully-packed egg sandwich
with seasonal fruits!

22
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:41,161
Enjoy!

23
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,831
It's finally the entrance ceremony today.

24
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:47,792
But isn't it starting in the afternoon?

25
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:49,836
It's still 10:00 a.m.

26
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:55,466
Are you getting too excited?

27
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,677
No! I was just taking a walk!

28
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:02,599
Well, it's nice to get excited.

29
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,061
There are a lot of interesting
guys there, after all.

30
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:09,355
I said I'm not excited!

31
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:13,192
Kotoha-san!

32
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,826
Oh, Nirei-chan! Good morning!

33
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,078
{\an8}Good morning, Granny Sato!

34
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:28,666
What do you think, Kotoha-san?

35
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:32,503
My Furin uniform look! Tight, ain't it?

36
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:35,548
You still have the tag on it.

37
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:38,218
Huh? Ah! You're right!

38
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:42,931
Huh? I can't get it off somehow.

39
00:03:44,682 --> 00:03:47,936
Silly me! I forgot to take off
the tag on my pants, too!

40
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:50,855
Huh? This guy's in Furin, too?

41
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,942
Yup. You two will be in the same grade.

42
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:55,693
What do you mean by this?

43
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:58,363
I've never seen you before, either!

44
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:01,032
Did you come from out of town?

45
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:03,952
I did. And what does it matter
where I came from?

46
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:06,287
Also! What's up with that?

47
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:08,331
That hair! And those eyes!

48
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:10,291
What?

49
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:13,127
Are they from stress?

50
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:15,088
You poor thing. You're still so young.

51
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:17,715
<i>Huh? Stress?</i>

52
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:19,092
<i>Stress?</i>

53
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:24,639
-Hey!
-Sorry, sorry!

54
00:04:24,722 --> 00:04:26,891
Nirei, this guy is Sakura.

55
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:29,102
He arrived in town yesterday.

56
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:31,479
And this is Nirei.

57
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:33,773
Sakura...

58
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:37,944
Never heard of any Sakura
from out of town.

59
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:40,947
Why would such a no-name kid come here?

60
00:04:41,155 --> 00:04:44,242
He doesn't have any ill intentions.
That's just how he is.

61
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:47,578
Furin High is no ordinary school!

62
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:48,871
Were you even aware?

63
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:54,085
<i>The people of Bofurin
stand up to protect the town.</i>

64
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:56,170
They defend the weak and crush evil!

65
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:58,131
They're real-life heroes!

66
00:04:58,214 --> 00:05:01,718
Everyone who comes to Furin
looks up to them

67
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:06,639
and wishes to join them to protect
the town! They're all cool people!

68
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:08,766
Of course, I'm one of those very people!

69
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:12,645
And yet, why would a nobody
who has no connection with the town

70
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:14,856
want to come to Furin?

71
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:20,653
So I can become the top there.

72
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:26,576
Yeah, heroes who defend the town
are cool and all.

73
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:30,204
And there seem to be quite a lot
of strong guys there.

74
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:33,291
If I can become the best among them...

75
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:36,169
that'd feel pretty satisfying.

76
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:43,426
That's impossible.
You could never make it.

77
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:47,930
If you say that...
If you actually try for it...

78
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:51,684
You'll go bald.

79
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:56,606
All right! Let's take this outside!

80
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:57,940
What's wrong?

81
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,942
Look at the time!

82
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:01,986
Kotoha-san, I'm heading out now!

83
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,071
Hey, hold up! Hey!

84
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:05,031
You're not having your usual breakfast?

85
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:07,700
-I only came to show off my uniform.
-Listen to me!

86
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:10,578
I'm doing three more rounds of patrol
before the ceremony!

87
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,292
Since I'll be joining the heroes
starting today!

88
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:22,173
Ouch!

89
00:06:22,256 --> 00:06:24,092
See? Pretty interesting guy, huh?

90
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:25,760
Yeah! Interesting all right!

91
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:28,846
A klutz who doesn't
listen to people, that is!

92
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,682
Plus, what the heck is wrong with him?
He's so lame.

93
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,601
Even guys like that are in Furin, too?

94
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:37,188
If they call themselves heroes,
they should look the part.

95
00:06:37,271 --> 00:06:41,234
Oh, I didn't expect
you'd criticize other people's fashion.

96
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:43,069
Do you want another cup of coffee?

97
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:44,779
I'm not talking about his clothes.

98
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:50,326
People like that who only care about their
looks are the first to run from a fight.

99
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:52,328
<i>They're as pathetic as they can be.</i>

100
00:06:52,411 --> 00:06:55,248
You sure talk like you know.

101
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:59,127
Because I have seen it a lot.
Enough times to make me sick.

102
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:01,838
I see.

103
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:04,006
Say, Sakura.

104
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:07,093
Do you know what color
the coffee fruit is?

105
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:14,725
Brown... like coffee?

106
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:16,561
It's red.

107
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:19,105
They're smooth, like cherries.

108
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:23,651
At first, I thought they were
the same as the ones they sold in jars.

109
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:27,905
I didn't even know that
those were actually the seeds.

110
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:30,575
You wouldn't know what something really is

111
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:33,161
if you're only looking at it
from one direction.

112
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:37,457
You're free to think however you want,
but aren't you being too quick to judge?

113
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:42,628
You should talk to them, look at them,
and try to understand them properly.

114
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:45,965
Or else you'll never know
what a person is really like.

115
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:50,470
<i>I'm facing you head-on.</i>

116
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:53,222
<i>So you should lift
your face up to us, too.</i>

117
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:55,892
Is he...

118
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,186
actually good at fighting?

119
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:00,897
Is that the only thing
that matters to you?

120
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,609
TONPU MARKET STREET

121
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:13,075
<i>You're free to think however you want,
but aren't you being too quick to judge?</i>

122
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:16,621
<i>Yeah, but I know I was right.</i>

123
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:22,210
Hey, kid! Do you want a loaf of bread?

124
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:23,961
They're fresh from the oven.

125
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,546
Huh? Why?

126
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:30,259
Why? Well, you Furin kids
are always helping us out.

127
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,803
So we want to give back as much as we can.

128
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:35,765
You're the boy who
fought here yesterday, right?

129
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:39,519
Everyone was talking about
how lucky we were to have you here.

130
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,313
I'm not hungry right now.

131
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:49,403
Then please, take some with you
and have it for lunch!

132
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:52,031
Our breads are still good
even when they're cold!

133
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:56,035
Have a nice day!

134
00:08:56,118 --> 00:08:58,913
Hey, boy! Thanks for yesterday!

135
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:02,041
Hey there, kid!
You were really cool back then.

136
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:03,876
{\an8}Hi, son! You're one strong kid!

137
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,462
{\an8}Wanna try competing in drinks
against this old man?

138
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,256
{\an8}Don't be silly, Dad!

139
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:14,303
<i>What the hell is going on?</i>

140
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:17,265
<i>What is wrong with everyone
in this town, anyway?</i>

141
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:21,269
<i>Aren't they acting too friendly
to a guy like me?</i>

142
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:24,397
<i>To a guy... like me?</i>

143
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:28,818
<i>Did I judge too early?</i>

144
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:32,572
<i>That there was no way
anyone would look at me like that...</i>

145
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,242
Excuse me!

146
00:09:37,201 --> 00:09:40,413
You're from Furin, right?
I need your help!

147
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:50,590
And here I was,
having fun chatting with a girl.

148
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:53,509
Why'd you try to get in my way?

149
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,845
That girl didn't want to talk to you!

150
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:58,556
What? Now you're making stuff up.

151
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:02,018
You punks call yourself Bofurin
and talk about protecting the town,

152
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,688
but if anything,
you are the one in need of protection.

153
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:07,273
Nice one!

154
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:18,159
Hey, you still don't get it?

155
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:21,078
You're not cut out to be a hero.

156
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:25,625
Go home and cry to your mommy!

157
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,001
You said it!

158
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:33,424
Listen, kid,
you're really testing my patience.

159
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:35,217
...will be purged...

160
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,094
Huh? What'd you say?

161
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:40,973
"Anyone past this point, who causes pain...
who brings destruction,

162
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:42,850
and holds evil in their heart,

163
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:47,271
will be purged by Bofurin
without exception!"

164
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:55,863
Only heroes on TV shows get stronger
by yelling their signature phrase.

165
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,285
Just give up already!

166
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,912
You're so persistent!

167
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:06,332
I don't care if you're called Bofurin
or Bowling, or whatever.

168
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:10,753
The one getting purged today is you!

169
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:26,852
Why are you saving me?

170
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:30,940
What the hell you think you're doing?

171
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:32,066
You're a Furin, too?

172
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:34,735
Here to save your friend, huh?
All by yourself?

173
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:37,571
Save? Friend?

174
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:39,782
Don't get the wrong idea, moron.

175
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:44,578
I just hate weaklings who act all smug,
thinking they're strong.

176
00:11:47,957 --> 00:11:49,542
They make me sick.

177
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:52,169
What did you say, you punk?

178
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:54,171
You can't take them on your own!

179
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:05,766
Wow...

180
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,687
<i>-In a flash...</i>
-You guys are freaking weak.

181
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:11,689
<i>In just the blink of an eye...</i>

182
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:13,691
<i>Who is this guy?</i>

183
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:22,283
Thank you very much.

184
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:25,035
You're disappointed, aren't you?

185
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:29,248
That a guy like me in Bofurin... in Furin...

186
00:12:29,331 --> 00:12:32,918
Don't get the wrong idea.
I didn't save you or anything.

187
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:35,796
You can find people trying
to look tough anywhere.

188
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:39,049
I don't know why you came to Furin,

189
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,427
but you better gauge your strength right.

190
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,553
I...

191
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:48,559
<i>have been treated as a gofer
and been beat up every single day</i>

192
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:50,144
<i>in middle school.</i>

193
00:12:50,227 --> 00:12:52,480
<i>All I could do was obey
everything I was told...</i>

194
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:57,902
<i>But the person who stepped in
to save me was someone from Furin.</i>

195
00:12:58,777 --> 00:13:02,156
<i>Normally, I would've been scared of him.</i>

196
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,700
<i>But he was really cool.</i>

197
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:07,786
I wanted to be just like him.

198
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:12,500
That's why I came to Furin, hoping
to be strong and cool just like him.

199
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:17,671
But I'm just pathetic.

200
00:13:22,801 --> 00:13:27,681
People like that who only care about their
looks are the first to run from a fight.

201
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:29,517
They're as pathetic as they can be.

202
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:33,979
"...will be purged by Bofurin
without exception!"

203
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:41,195
You already can't fight.
Don't be a crybaby, too.

204
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:43,197
It's gonna make you look weaker.

205
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:45,241
But well...

206
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,118
I suppose you're not all that pathetic.

207
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:52,081
Um, are you okay?

208
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:55,918
Huh? I'm perfectly fine!

209
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:57,169
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO TALK TO YOU!

210
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,380
I was so scared when they grabbed my arm,

211
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:01,840
but I'm grateful you were there!

212
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:04,260
Thank you so much.

213
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:10,933
And you too! Thank you!

214
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:16,272
Sakura!

215
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:18,232
...-san.

216
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:21,151
What is it?

217
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:23,237
Well, uh...

218
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:26,657
CONFIDENTIAL

219
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:29,243
What's your height, weight, blood type,

220
00:14:29,326 --> 00:14:31,495
hobbies, skills, and preferred type?

221
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:34,957
You're just a bit taller than me,
around 169cm.

222
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,918
You've got a lot of muscles
and very little fat. About 59kg?

223
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:41,005
{\an8}Your foot size is 26.5.
You've still got a lot to grow!

224
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:44,633
-Gross! Don't touch me! Don't measure me!
-Sorry.

225
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:49,889
I love gathering data on people
that I think are super cool.

226
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,807
Do whatever you want!

227
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:54,518
Okay! I'll watch you up close!

228
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:59,189
And while I'm at it,
let me show you around!

229
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:00,316
Huh?

230
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:03,110
Are you trying to say
I don't know the way to the school?

231
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:05,029
No, not that!

232
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:07,823
I might not be able
to help much in fights,

233
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:10,492
but I can show you around
the town and its people.

234
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:14,246
All the way to the top!

235
00:15:16,832 --> 00:15:18,918
Come on! The school is this way!

236
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:21,795
Hey, don't touch me! Don't drag me!

237
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:24,048
Listen to me, damn it!

238
00:15:30,137 --> 00:15:32,723
FURIN HIGH SCHOOL

239
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:34,767
BOFURIN

240
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:40,606
Welcome, first-years.

241
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:46,070
Hey, come on! Let's hurry!

242
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:48,822
Shut up. I get hungry after a fight, okay?

243
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:50,449
This bread's good!

244
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:54,703
Oh, That bread's from Cactus, right?
The bread there is great even when cold!

245
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,038
Wait, that's not it.

246
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,915
Anyway, let's go!

247
00:15:58,874 --> 00:16:01,752
Sakura-san! Hurry, hurry!

248
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:05,089
If you're in such a rush,
just go by yourself.

249
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:12,846
BOFURIN

250
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,556
<i>That's a lot of them.</i>

251
00:16:15,557 --> 00:16:17,559
Sakura-san!

252
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:25,359
{\an8}This is the Bofurin headquarters!
I'm so excited!

253
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:29,655
<i>There are a lot of people
just like them here, huh?</i>

254
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:33,158
Sakura-san, there it is!

255
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:34,994
There is what?

256
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:37,246
The class lists!

257
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:38,998
What's up with this sign?

258
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:41,875
Let's see...

259
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:46,088
Yay! Sakura-san, we're in the same class!

260
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:48,590
Yeah, yeah. I got it.

261
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:50,968
I wonder who else will be there.

262
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:55,139
Huh? There's Suo-san! And Kiryu-san!
And even Tsugeura-san?

263
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:56,724
You know them?

264
00:16:56,807 --> 00:16:58,100
Nope, not at all!

265
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:00,477
But they're all amazing people!

266
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:02,604
-Let me explain from Suo-sa...
-Enough.

267
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:05,232
Don't get so excited from
just looking at a damn list.

268
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:09,278
-It doesn't matter who we're stuck with.
-What are you saying, Sakura-san?

269
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:13,157
It's very important to know who
we're going to be in class with...

270
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:15,909
Huh? What's wrong?

271
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,661
You're kidding me...

272
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:20,748
-No way. Are you serious?
-Hey, what's the matter?

273
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:25,627
Out of all people... we ended up with him?

274
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:28,338
Where did all that excitement
from earlier go?

275
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:30,507
Don't tell me you wanna
go home after com...

276
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:31,592
Sakura-san.

277
00:17:32,217 --> 00:17:34,803
Can you promise me one thing?

278
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:36,013
Promise?

279
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:40,142
Please be nice to everyone in class.

280
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:42,519
You gotta smile! Smile!

281
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:44,396
Huh? Are you messing with me?

282
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,939
I'm serious!

283
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:51,612
Listen, everyone in Bofurin
gathered here to protect the town.

284
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:52,529
FURIN

285
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:55,699
<i>So it wouldn't be surprising
if someone don't think</i>

286
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:59,036
<i>too fondly of those
from out of town like you.</i>

287
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,332
I think it's important for you
to have people understand that

288
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:06,376
you're not here to harm the town
and not an enemy of Bofurin!

289
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:08,003
So please...

290
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:10,923
What are you doing?

291
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:12,174
Warmups.

292
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:13,092
Why?

293
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:16,428
I don't know how strong
the guys behind that door are.

294
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:18,013
So I better get myself ready.

295
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:20,349
Were you even listening
to what I just said?

296
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:22,351
You're an outsider!

297
00:18:22,434 --> 00:18:25,187
One little misunderstanding
could get this whole class...

298
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:29,817
no, this whole school to
treat you like their enemy!

299
00:18:31,985 --> 00:18:35,405
I don't care if they
think of me as an enemy.

300
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:41,703
I came here to fight my way to the top.

301
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:53,423
<i>They're all glaring at us!
Ow, ow, ow! It hurts!</i>

302
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:01,557
Not bad.

303
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:02,516
Hey!

304
00:19:04,059 --> 00:19:05,894
You must be Sakura-kun.

305
00:19:07,104 --> 00:19:08,730
What about it?

306
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:09,898
Who are you?

307
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:11,316
Don't do that!

308
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,902
I'm sorry! He's just very excitable!

309
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:15,612
More importantly, you...

310
00:19:16,196 --> 00:19:18,615
An eyepatch and long tassel earrings!

311
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:21,160
There's no doubt about it!

312
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:23,453
I'm Leonardo DiCaprio!

313
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:26,707
You're a foreigner?

314
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:28,625
I am...

315
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:31,128
-That's what got you?
-Nope, I'm Japanese.

316
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:34,339
<i>I didn't know he's the type
to make a joke like that.</i>

317
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:37,092
<i>I thought he'd be more aloof and cold.</i>

318
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,096
You're Suo-san, right?

319
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:44,183
Yup. That's what everyone calls me.

320
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:46,768
By the way, this eyepatch is to seal...

321
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:49,813
an ancient Chinese spirit inside.

322
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,149
Wasn't it because of a past accident?

323
00:19:52,232 --> 00:19:54,651
Yup. That's what everyone says.

324
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:57,154
What? He's just a habitual liar!

325
00:19:57,237 --> 00:20:00,866
Wait! Among the first-years,
he's actually...

326
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,244
That's enough about me.

327
00:20:04,661 --> 00:20:07,664
Sakura-kun. Let's talk about you.

328
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:14,046
<i>Shoot. People from out of town
are really treated as outsiders here.</i>

329
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:18,217
<i>Is it impossible for him
to be accepted here?</i>

330
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,761
I heard all about it!
You were amazing back there!

331
00:20:20,844 --> 00:20:23,889
You're the star of that fight
on main street yesterday, right?

332
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,891
Fight on main street yesterday?

333
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:29,019
What are you talking about, Suo?
Who is that guy?

334
00:20:29,102 --> 00:20:34,107
You guys heard about the clash with
Spaltips yesterday on main street, right?

335
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:36,151
Hiragi-san and the others went there,

336
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:39,363
but the first one to show up
and protect the town was...

337
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,241
Sakura-kun!

338
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:44,868
Did you really, Sakura-san?

339
00:20:45,994 --> 00:20:46,912
For real?

340
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:51,917
I heard Hiragi-san go, so I was
relieved and didn't listen to the rest.

341
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,918
Same here.

342
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:55,045
My grandma was there, apparently.

343
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:58,465
She said there was a guy she didn't
recognize wearing Furin uniform.

344
00:20:58,548 --> 00:21:01,176
I knew someone new moved into town,
but way to go, man!

345
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,387
You did great before school even started!

346
00:21:04,805 --> 00:21:06,223
Too close...

347
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,600
<i>Looks like we managed for now...</i>

348
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:10,227
<i>Nice job, Sakura-san!</i>

349
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:14,940
<i>Now Sakura-san won't be seen
as an enemy to Bofurin, at least.</i>

350
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:17,109
<i>I'm sure it'll be okay with that guy, too...</i>

351
00:21:17,192 --> 00:21:21,071
But why did you come all the way here
from outside town?

352
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:24,074
I came here to be the top.

353
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:33,542
Wait, please!

354
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:36,044
He doesn't mean that
he's gonna pick a fight

355
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,755
or beat anyone up!

356
00:21:38,922 --> 00:21:40,966
-Yes, I do.
-Can you shut up for a sec?

357
00:21:57,482 --> 00:22:00,277
Sakura-san! Please! Anyone but him!

358
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:04,865
He's undoubtedly the most dangerous guy
in our grade... No, in the whole school!

359
00:22:04,948 --> 00:22:07,492
He's Kyotaro Sugishita!

360
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:08,618
Sugishita?

361
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:09,703
Hey.

362
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:11,163
Dangerous guy?

363
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:12,873
They're my favorite.

364
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,295
I'll crush you.

365
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:26,511
Phew, you almost got caught in that.

366
00:22:27,929 --> 00:22:29,222
{\an8}Nice.

367
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:32,476
{\an8}I expected no less from Furin High.

368
00:22:34,561 --> 00:22:36,354
Now we're talking.

369
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:33,745
Sakura-san! You shouldn't do that?

370
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,413
Shouldn't do what?

371
00:23:35,497 --> 00:23:37,958
You threw all the food
you got from everyone

372
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:40,377
in the shopping district before you fight!

373
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:44,714
I only threw that on reflex to save you.

374
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:47,551
This is this. That is that.

375
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:51,930
Besides, after that...

376
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:54,182
I picked them all up and ate them.

377
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:58,937
You're surprisingly upright,
huh, Sakura-san?

